          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
          Ukraine-US agreement
        </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/us-ukraine-natural-resources-deal-access.png" alt="Months in the making, the US and Ukraine have signed a deal that will give Washington access to some of the war-torn country's natural resources" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Months in the making, the US and Ukraine have signed a deal that will give Washington access to some of the war-torn country's natural resources. Credits: Yulia Svyrydenko/Facebook/Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           The United States and Ukraine have <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-2-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-signed-a-historic-agreement" target="_blank">signed a historic agreement</a> that allows the US to tap into Ukraine‚Äôs natural resources, including rare earth elements, oil, and gas. This agreement also grants Ukraine full ownership of these resources and aims to boost capital and reconstruction in Ukraine. Here are some takeaways:</p>
          
         </mj-text>
        
         <mj-table font-family="Roboto+Serif" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" padding="10px 18px 10px 18px" style=" width:100%;">
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">‚Üí</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">It sets up a fund to manage US involvement and support</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">‚Üí</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Ukraine does not have to repay any of the estimated $350B in aid. Ukrainian officials view this as a significant concession from the United States</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">‚Üí</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The agreement supports Ukraine‚Äôs goal of becoming an EU member. It doesn‚Äôt explicitly state that Ukraine‚Äôs EU accession will come across as a conflict of interest</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">‚Üí</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The US also confirmed ongoing military support, including air defense systems, but no formal security guarantees are in place</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="font-size:18px; width:20px; vertical-align: top; padding-right:8px;">‚Üí</td>
              <td style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">A key provision, emphasized by Ukraine but not included in the signed text, stipulates that for the first 10 years, all gains will be reinvested in Ukraine‚Äôs economy</td>
            </tr>
        </mj-table>


          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         The US Treasury views this agreement as a symbol of partnership and a potential means to recover past aid and military support. The language used by the US in the announcement is also notably harsher towards Russia. This agreement could begin many cooperations between Russia and Ukraine. 
         </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          <i>Read the full text of the agreement <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-2-may-25-spotlight-h1-2-here" target="_blank">here</a>.</i>
         </p>
        
