          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Modi goes Latin</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/india-latin-america-mineral-investment-expansion.png" alt="India is ramping up its Latin America presence to tap the region‚Äôs vast mineral reserves" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>India is ramping up its Latin America presence to tap the region‚Äôs vast mineral reserves. Credits: Adnan Abidi/Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Indian PM Narendra Modi's ambition to achieve net-zero carbon emissions by 2070 has led him to Latin America. Modi is looking to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-2-may-25-spotlight-h2-3-secure-essential-minerals" target="_blank">secure essential minerals</a> for India‚Äôs green energy goals. Latin America has the world‚Äôs largest lithium reserves, especially in the ‚Äúlithium triangle‚Äù of Argentina, Bolivia, and Chile. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Modi discussed securing a long-term stock of minerals, such as lithium and copper, with Chilean President Gabriel Boric. Chile‚Äôs state-run copper company, Codelco, will supply copper concentrates to Hindustan Copper and the Adani Group. Codelco is working to supply lithium to India‚Äôs expanding electric vehicle market.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          India is expanding in Latin America by establishing embassies in lithium-rich countries. It has formed agreements, such as one with Argentina to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-2-may-25-spotlight-h2-4-lease-lithium" target="_blank">lease lithium</a> exploration blocks. Despite competition from China for these vital minerals, experts feel this mineral rush is about boosting India‚Äôs role in the global supply chain of the energy transition.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
