          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üá∏üá¨ Singapore‚Äôs ruling party woos youth</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Singapore‚Äôs ruling party, the People‚Äôs Action Party, is giving its traditional image a makeover to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-2-may-25-worldwide-h2-7-attract-younger-voters" target="_blank">attract younger voters</a> ahead of the upcoming general election. The party is  tapping into social media trends to target this demographic. They share TikTok skits, participate in podcast interviews, and collaborate with influencers. PM Lawrence Wong has showcased his guitar skills and discussed budgets at a cat caf√©.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Despite its strong history, the party is losing support among youth who worry about rising living expenses, housing, and job opportunities. Opposition parties are also active on social media, but they have fewer resources at their disposal. Younger Singaporean voters prioritize effective policy solutions and genuine personal connections over digital popularity.</p>
